            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001929_0001" n="0001"/>
<opener>
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#U"><!-- diagonal -->Enclosure sent
<lb/>via <unclear cert="low">N.S Field</unclear></add>
<lb/><dateline rend="right"><placeName><geogName type="cataracts">Cataracts of the <placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName></geogName></placeName> 
<lb/><date when="1863-07-03">3 July 1863</date></dateline>
<!--I can't tell whether Livingstone wrote part or all of this line and the marginal note. I assumed no in my coding. He appeared to be running out of ink by the end so that could account for the gray and tiny handwriting. -AA --><!-- It's another hand here and elsewhere, as noted. AW -->
<lb/><add place="inspace" hand="#U"><choice><abbr>Rec<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi></abbr><expan>Received</expan></choice> <date when="1866-03-27">27 March 1864</date></add>    
<lb/><salute>Dear Sir</salute>
</opener>
<lb/><p>Though I have
<lb/>not the pleasure
<lb/>of knowing you
<lb/>personally you
<lb/>were an acquaintance
<lb/>of my late good
<lb/>wife and on this
<lb/>light plea I take
<lb/>the liberty of asking
<lb/>your friendly office
            	
	<pb facs="liv_001929_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>for our son <persName>Robert
<lb/>Moffat Livingstone</persName>
<lb/>who I hear has come
<lb/>out to <placeName><settlement><region>Natal</region></settlement></placeName> in
<lb/>order to join me
<lb/>We are recalled by
<lb/>to <choice><abbr>M.</abbr><expan>Majesty's</expan></choice> Government
<lb/>a thing fully expected
<lb/>when we found
<lb/>that the <term type="nationality">Portuguese</term>
<lb/><term type="occupation">slave hunters</term> of 
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Tette</settlement></placeName> 
<lb/>aided by a drought
<lb/>had completely
<lb/>depopulated the
<lb/>whole <placeName><geogName type="valley">Shire Valley</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>They ended our work	

	<pb facs="liv_001929_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>and the people together
<lb/>though it may not
<lb/>be politic to put this
<lb/>as the real reason
<lb/>of the <choice><sic>recal</sic><corr>recall</corr></choice>. Pity
<lb/>we ever believed
<lb/>in <term type="nationality">Portuguese</term>
<lb/>professions of desire
<lb/>for the civilization
<lb/>of <placeName><bloc>Africa</bloc></placeName> as with
<lb/>half the labour &amp;
<lb/>expense we could
<lb/>have done more
<lb/>at the <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>though it has
<lb/>water for navigation
<lb/>for only about <unclear cert="low">a few</unclear>	
	
	<pb facs="liv_001929_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>months of the year. It
<lb/>has a <unclear cert="medium">fine</unclear> month &amp;
<lb/>this <placeName><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName></placeName> is the
<lb/>terror of all naval
<lb/>officers, but we
<lb/>are going away in
<lb/>January next &amp;
<lb/>should <persName>Robert</persName> not
<lb/>have an opportunity
<lb/>of coming up to
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Quillimane</settlement></placeName>, <placeName><country>Mozambique</country></placeName>, 
<lb/>or <placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> before
<lb/>that will you direct
<lb/>him, to any situation
<lb/>in which he can
<lb/>earn an honest
<lb/>livelihood - <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Rae</persName>
	
	<pb facs="liv_001929_0005" n="0005"/>
<lb/>knows him better
<lb/>than I do and thinks
<lb/>him clever enough
<lb/>for any ordinary
<lb/>work but of this
<lb/>you will perhaps be
<lb/>a better judge. I
<lb/>wished to give him
<lb/>a university education
<lb/>and then let him
<lb/>shift for himself
<lb/>but this seems to
<lb/>be against the grain
<lb/>and should he settle
<lb/>to anything now
<lb/>it may be best in
<lb/>the long run.</p>
            	
	<pb facs="liv_001929_0006" n="0006"/>
<lb/><p>Any expenses that
<lb/>you can sanction
<lb/>I shall cheerfully
<lb/>pay - and if you
<lb/>kindly give him
<lb/>a good word to
<lb/>avoid evil company
<lb/>drink &amp;c.<!--and cetera again -AA --><!-- OK, no need to keep pointing this out. AW --> you
<lb/>will confer a
<lb/>great favour on</p>
<closer>
<lb/><salute>yours most sincerely</salute>
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed>
</closer>
	</div>

